enum SystemsBiologyWorkbench::dataBlockType
 

Datatypes used in C++ API.

uses standard encoding of datatypes used in both the API and in datablocks.

Enumeration values:
ByteType  C++ API type - unsigned char.
IntegerType  C++ API type - Integer.
DoubleType  C++ API type - Double.
BooleanType  C++ API type - bool.
StringType  C++ API type - char *.
ArrayType  C++ API type - <T>* or <T>**, std::vector<T>, std::deque<T> or std::list<T>.
ListType  C++ API type - DataBlockReader * or DataBlockWriter *.
VoidType  placeholder when no value is returned from a method.
TerminateType  value of last byte in a datablock or message.
ErrorType  placeholder when error has occured in an API function.

Definition at line 97 of file sbwenums.h.

enum SystemsBiologyWorkbench::ExceptionCode
 

Exception types used in C++ API.

uses standard encoding of exceptions used in both in the API and in exception messages.

Enumeration values:
ApplicationExceptionCode  generated by a module ie not raised by the infastructure.
RawExceptionCode  generated by a OS or unhandled exception.
CommunicationExceptionCode  communication between modules has been disrupted.
ModuleStartExceptionCode  unable to start module when a new module instance was required.
TypeMismatchExceptionCode  the data contained in a datablock doesn't correspond to the requested type.
IncompatibleMethodSignatureExceptionCode  two method signatures do not match.
ModuleIdSyntaxExceptionCode  the syntax of a module instance identifier string is incorrect.
IncorrectCategorySyntaxExceptionCode  the syntax of a service category string is incorrect.
ServiceNotFoundExceptionCode  the requested service doesn't exist.
MethodTypeNotBlockTypeExceptionCode  thrown during communications if a supplied class uses types which are not data block types (not raised in C++ library).
MethodAmbiguousExceptionCode  the given signature matches more than one method on a service.
UnsupportedObjectTypeExceptionCode  the given valid type is not supported by a client library.
MethodNotFoundExceptionCode  the given signature or name doesn't match any method on a service.
SignatureSyntaxExceptionCode  the syntax of the given signature is incorrect.
ModuleDefinitionExceptionCode  exception thrown when an attempt to define a new module fails.
ModuleNotFoundExceptionCode  the requested module doesn't exist.
BrokerStartExceptionCode  unable to start broker.

Definition at line 72 of file sbwenums.h.

enum SystemsBiologyWorkbench::moduleManagementType
 

The ways in which a given module can be managed by the broker.

Uses standard encoding used by both by the API and the broker interface.

Enumeration values:
UniqueModule  broker only creates one instance of the module and refers all requests to that instance.
SelfManagedModule  broker creates a new instance for each module instance request.
